        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "Collaborative Learning",
          "Grades (Weekly or Final)",
          "A vs B or C",
          "75 graduate students",
          "1 Software Engineering Course ",
          "GitLab commits, GitLab issues ",
          "[Vertices (students), Edges (interactions between vertexes)]",
          "Every Week - total 16 weeks",
          "Authors create a set of graph nodes to represent learners and their interactions in a collaborative learning environment.\n\nThe first part is related with the definition of interaction degrees, which leads to the generation of an Interaction Matrix - that represents the vertexes and interactions.\n\nFrom the interaction graph, the model predicts the grade that the learner should get that week → based on contributions and/or interactions.\n\nThen, it follows a standard ML pipeline: \n\n- Generation, \n- Variable Selection,\nModelling",
          "AdaBoost, R-GCN, GTN, Graph Trans, CLGT",
          "Temporal Cross-Validation",
          "{Accuracy: 0.7392 - CLGT, F1-Score: 0.6675 - CLGT, AUC: 0.9057 - CLGT}",
          "Authors create a new Graph Transformer and compare its performance versus other models used.\n\nEssencially, the goal of the models is to make a prediction for every Node (each week’s grade and/or final grade) and the model outperforms (on average) the remaining tested models.\n\n",
          "- Single Course Study\n\n- Specific to Collaborative Learning Settings using GitLab\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 7
    }
  ],
